<p>I'm trying to set up SSL on RabbitMQ on a Windows 2008 R2 server. I follow the instructions <a href="https://www.rabbitmq.com/ssl.html" rel="nofollow">here</a> to have all the certs set up. I verify the server is listening on 5671 in the log:</p>  <pre><code>=INFO REPORT==== 1-Oct-2015::12:31:01 === started TCP Listener on [::]:5672  =INFO REPORT==== 1-Oct-2015::12:31:01 === started TCP Listener on 0.0.0.0:5672  =INFO REPORT==== 1-Oct-2015::12:31:01 === started SSL Listener on [::]:5671  =INFO REPORT==== 1-Oct-2015::12:31:01 === started SSL Listener on 0.0.0.0:5671 </code></pre>  <p>Then I try to use the code from the same link above to send a message. Here's my code:</p>  <pre><code>    ConnectionFactory cf = new ConnectionFactory();      cf.Ssl.ServerName = "myserver.mydomain.com";     cf.Ssl.CertPath = @"c:\temp\testca\client\keycert.p12";     cf.Ssl.CertPassphrase = "mypassword";     cf.Ssl.Enabled = true;      using (IConnection conn = cf.CreateConnection())     {         using (IModel ch = conn.CreateModel())         {             ch.QueueDeclare("rabbitmq-dotnet-test", false, false, false, null);             ch.BasicPublish("",                             "rabbitmq-dotnet-test",                             null,                             Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes("Hello, World"));         }    } </code></pre>  <p>However, I get the following error on CreateConnection():</p>  <pre><code>No connection could be made because the target machine actively refused it 127.0.0.1:5671 </code></pre>  <p>What am I missing?</p>